com.camerontec.catalys.server.adapter.emx.processor

Class EMXFileSession

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.camerontec.catalys.server.adapter.emx.processor.EMXFileSession
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Runnable

    public abstract class EMXFileSession
extends Object
implements Runnable
    An instance of the EMXFileSession is created by an instance of an EMXFileAdapter and is linked to by all of the instances of EMXFileAdapter which serve the same party (typically two, one in the outgoing message processor chain and one in the incoming chain).

    It is the EMXFileSession that does all of the work. The EMXFileAdapter is a facade that allows multiple instances to connect to the same underlying EMXFileSession.

    Author:
    Christopher J Burton, 09/Jun/2002.

      • run

        public void run()
        The run method's tasks are: 1. Look to see if a new file of outgoing messages is waiting to be processed. 2. Switch to a new set of incoming message files if a timer has passed or a flag has been set. Note that a different instance of Thread will be created for each connection (as made by the onConnectionStatus method above). Only one Thread instance will exist at a time, but the EMXFileSession object will, in general, persist across many different calls of this run() method.
        Specified by:
        run in interface Runnable

      • readAcknowledgedReferences

        protected abstract void readAcknowledgedReferences(File file,
                                                   int emxMsgIDCode)
        Read all of the acknowledged references in the supplied MACK/MERR file and add them to the set of acknowledged references. This is used in recovery processing. Each concrete subclass must implement this method so that it adds every reference in any supplied file to the member variable activeAcknowledgedReferences.
        Parameters:
        file - A file containing MACK or MERR acknowledgements that have been received for an active file.
        emxMsgIDCode - An indicator of whether the file contains MACKs or MERRs.

      • makeFileActive

        protected abstract boolean makeFileActive(String readyFileName,
                                          String extn)
        Make the specified file the currently active file. Also define MACK and MERR files to collect the acknowledgement responses from EMX. We assume that the name of the readyFile is in the form "TTTT.id.tsv", where TTTT is "OINP", "VREQ", etc. We will create MACK and MERR acknowledgement files named "MACK.ACKS.id.tsv" and "MERR.ACKS.id.tsv". The ".ACKS" is necessary to distinguish the file as an acknowledgement file and prevent it from being sent! A Product Provider might well need to send a file called "MERR.id.tsv", for example.
        Parameters:
        readyFileName - The name of the file to be made active.
        extn - The extension of the file to be made active. Under normal processing this will be extnReady, but during recovery processing it will be extnActive.
        Returns:
        true if we were able to make the file active.

      • markActiveFileDone

        protected final void markActiveFileDone(String extnNew,
                                        boolean acksDelay)
        Call this method when the current active file is known to be completely processed.

        This variation has an "acksDelay" parameter which, if set, causes a delay to be forced between marking the outgoing file as "done" and changing the acknowledgement file set. This is for use when dealing with a file type such as CSMD, where we don't expect acknowledgements of every sent message but may receive MERRs to some messages. We want to allow time for any MERRs to arrive before allowing the program to proceed to send another outgoing file.

        Parameters:
        extnNew - the new file extension
        acksDelay - whether a delay has been specified

      • changeAcknowledgementFileSet

        protected abstract void changeAcknowledgementFileSet(String id)
        Change the names of the acknowledgement files, making any previously current acknowledgement files ready. If an ID is supplied, the files will be named with that ID. Otherwise a timestamp is used, which is useful for preparing acknowledgement files that will receive unsolicited acknowledgements.
        Parameters:
        id - an id

      • changeIncomingFileSet

        protected void changeIncomingFileSet()
        This method is called whenever a new file set must be started. It doesn't open or close any files. It just defines File objects for each file that will be used if a message of that type arrives. The method is synchronized because it is important to ensure that the processEMXMessage() method has no data file open when this method runs, or otherwise a rename operation may fail.
